The paper deals with graph theory and algorithms for computing graph invariants, such as diameter and radius, on various subclasses of graphs. The Helly property, which is the main focus of the paper, is a geometric property of graphs that has been extensively studied in computational geometry and has applications in various areas of computer science. Therefore, cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.CG (Computational Geometry) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also involves algorithms and complexity analysis, which suggests cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity) as likely sub-categories. Finally, the paper deals with graph classes such as chordal graphs and split graphs, which are studied in cs.GT (Graph Theory).
